"# Elf, Drow \n"
"_Medium humanoid (elf), neutral evil_\n"
"**Armor Class** 15 (chain shirt)    \n"
"**Hit Points** 13 (3d8)    \n"
"**Speed** 30 ft. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/elf_drow.md:14
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| STR     | DEX     | CON     | INT     | WIS     | CHA     |\n"
"|---------|---------|---------|---------|---------|---------|\n"
"| 10 (+0) | 14 (+2) | 10 (+0) | 11 (+0) | 11 (+0) | 12 (+1) |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/elf_drow.md:19
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Skills** Perception +2, Stealth +4    \n"
"**Senses** darkvision 120 ft., passive Perception 12    \n"
"**Languages** Elvish, Undercommon    \n"
"**Challenge** 1/4 (50 XP) \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/elf_drow.md:25
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Fey Ancestry.** The drow has advantage on saving throws against being "
"charmed, and magic can't put the drow to sleep.    \n"
"**Innate Spellcasting.** The drow's spellcasting ability is Charisma (spell "
"save DC 11). It can innately cast the following spells, requiring no "
"material components:    \n"
"At will: **_dancing lights_**    \n"
"1/day each: **_darkness_**, **_faerie fire_**    \n"
"**Sunlight Sensitivity.** While in sunlight, the drow has disadvantage on "
"attack rolls, as well as on Wisdom (Perception) checks that rely on "
"sight. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/elf_drow.md:28
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"### Actions \n"
"**Shortsword.** _Melee Weapon Attack:_ +4 to hit, reach 5 ft., one "
"target. _Hit:_ 5 (1d6 + 2) piercing damage.    \n"
"**Hand Crossbow.** _Ranged Weapon Attack:_ +4 to hit, range 30/120 ft., one "
"target. _Hit:_ 5 (1d6 + 2) piercing damage, and the target must succeed on a "
"DC 13 Constitution saving throw or be poisoned for 1 hour. If the saving "
"throw fails by 5 or more, the target is also unconscious while poisoned in "
"this way. The target wakes up if it takes damage or if another creature "
"takes an action to shake it awake.\n"
msgstr ""
